Suspected anthrax on farm
-------------------------
The lethal disease anthrax has been detected on a farm near Varberg,
Halland. 13 cows have died since November 29 [2008], according to the home
page of Sweden's Ministry of Agriculture.

Anthrax can carry from animal to human, but it is not common. The bacteria
does not carry from human to human. The farm, now closed, has about 70
animals. The public has no access to the premises and nothing can be sold
from it. Since the disease can carry from animal to human the people who
have been in contact with the animals have received antibiotics.

"It's not a funny decease. It can be deadly for humans, says Bengt Larsson,
director of infectious diseases, Ministry of Agriculture to TT
(Tidningarnas Telegrambyr - Swedish news agency). The last anthrax outbreak
in Sweden was in 1981 in Uppland (region in central Sweden, north of
Stockholm).

Contact person: Bengt Marsson can be reached on +46-70-290 37 53.

